# Pinky core

- Match existing project style. Prefer the smallest diff that solves the task.
- No drive-by refactors, unrelated cleanups, or unsolicited new abstractions.
- Never commit secrets. Use env vars / secret managers.
- Ask when requirements are ambiguous; explore the codebase before inventing APIs.
- Respect user scope: only change what was asked.
